FBIS4-1468 "drafr083_b_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-083 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Mogadishu Airport Security `Guaranteed' Mogadishu Airport Security `Guaranteed' EA2504200094 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 25 Apr 94 EA2504200094 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the Great Somali People Somali BFN [Text] Hassan Mohamed Nur Qalaad, a member of the Popular Defense Committee, has reported on the security situation of Mogadishu Airport. Mr. Qalaad and other officials, who were on a working tour to check security at important sites including Mogadishu Airport and its surroundings, said the security of these areas was very good and there was no problem whatsoever. The officials, who included Khalif Dhunkaal and Abdulahi Shire Ugas, alias Anabodhe, said that Mogadishu Airport was for all Somali people and was important for social work. Therefore, its security had been fully guaranteed. They added that social work had started at the airport and no insecurity was observed. Flights from Mogadishu Airport had now begun properly. Finally, the officials called on Somali people in general, and those living in Mogadishu city in particular, to be calm and participate in the reconstruction of their country.
